21/05/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Leading a Serbian delegation Tuesday (20 May), Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic was assured by high-ranking EU and NATO officials that Serbia would advance steadily towards Euro-Atlantic integration. 
In turn, Zivkovic said the government is strongly committed to progress towards EU integration. 
As for NATO, Secretary General George Robertson urged increased war crimes co-operation efforts as a condition for entering the Partnership for Peace initiative.
In other news Tuesday, Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Boris Tadic visited Berlin and said that his country is looking for help from NATO countries in developing a new defence policy. 
He invited Germany to take part in the effort, along with the United States, Britain, Spain, Norway and Slovakia. 
(B92, BBC, Beta, FoNet, Tanjug, AFP - 20/05/03)
